# Trump-Iran April 14, 2026 вҖ” New YouTube Short

## Goal

Create a **new 1-minute YouTube Short** covering the Trump-Iran crisis as of **April 14, 2026**. The video uses a **formal, documentary narrative** with real news data from Tavily, Reddit community sentiment, and a premium broadcast-style visual layout with word-by-word caption animation.

This is a **new composition** (`trump-iran-apr14`), separate from the existing `trump-iran-short`.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Narrative Tone:** Formal & documentary вҖ” no hype language, no "Reddit is losing its mind" style. Think BBC/Reuters/Al Jazeera documentary narration.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Duration:** Strictly ~60 seconds. 8 scenes at ~7.5s each. Audio at normal 1Г— speed (no 1.5Г— acceleration).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Images:** Real news images fetched via Tavily API for each scene. Each image will be positioned as a **full-bleed background** with Ken Burns zoom + dark gradient overlay for text readability. AI-generated fallback images will be created for any scenes where Tavily fails to return usable photos.

---

## News Content (April 14, 2026 вҖ” Today)

### Tavily Research Summary
| # | Scene | Key Fact | Source |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Dateline Hook** | "April 14, 2026 вҖ” The US-Iran standoff enters its most critical phase." | Multiple |
| 2 | **Blockade Active** | US naval blockade of Iranian ports & Strait of Hormuz began April 13. Trump: vessels approaching will be "immediately eliminated." | Washington Post, CFR |
| 3 | **Talks Collapsed** | 21-hour marathon in Islamabad ended in deadlock. US demands 20-year enrichment freeze; Iran counters with 5 years. | Time, Al Jazeera |
| 4 | **Oil Shock** | Brent crude surged 7%, hitting $104/barrel. Analysts warn $110+ if blockade holds. IMF downgrades Middle East growth forecasts. | Economic Times |
| 5 | **Iran's Response** | Iran calls blockade "piracy." Threatens retaliation against Persian Gulf ports. IRGC on high alert. | KSAT, Gulf News |
| 6 | **World Reacts** | France & UK planning naval escort conference. Pakistan offers to host Round 2 talks. Turkey & Egypt mediating. | CFR, Time |
| 7 | **Reddit Sentiment** | r/worldnews: "Reckless." Strategic skepticism, concerns over civilian harm, criticism of "limited operation" labeling to bypass Congress. Market manipulation fears. | Reddit, LSE |
| 8 | **Countdown CTA** | Ceasefire expires April 21. 7 days remain. Both sides may return to talks Thursday. | Washington Post |

### Reddit Sentiment (Curated)
- **Strategic Skepticism:** "Performative action вҖ” threats and negotiations are market manipulation theater."
- **Civilian Harm Concern:** "Total war rhetoric violates international law. Civilians always pay."
- **Congressional Bypass:** "'Limited operation' is a deliberate attempt to avoid war authorization."

