## Proposed Changes

### 1. Image Pipeline

#### [NEW] [fetch-images-apr14.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/AInewsvideo/scripts/fetch-images-apr14.ts)
- Adapted from existing `fetch-images-tavily.ts`
- 8 scene-specific Tavily queries targeting April 14 headlines
- Downloads to `public/images/trump-iran-apr14/`
- Fallback queries if primary returns no results

#### [NEW] AI-Generated Fallback Images
- For any scenes where Tavily returns no usable photos, use `generate_image` tool to create formal news-style backgrounds
- Style: dark, moody, photojournalistic вҖ” no cartoon/illustration

---

### 2. Voiceover Pipeline

#### [NEW] [generate-voiceover-apr14.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/AInewsvideo/scripts/generate-voiceover-apr14.ts)
- 8 scenes, formal documentary narration
- Voice: `pNInz6obpgDQGcFmaJgB` (Adam вҖ” authoritative)
- ElevenLabs `eleven_flash_v2_5` model
- Voice settings: stability=0.55, similarity_boost=0.80, style=0.20 (more formal, less dramatic)
- Output: `public/voiceover/trump-iran-apr14/s01-dateline.mp3` ... `s08-countdown.mp3`

**Scene scripts (formal tone):**

| Scene | Voiceover Text (~7-8s each) |
|---|---|
| s01-dateline | "April fourteenth, twenty twenty-six. The United States and Iran have entered the most dangerous phase of their confrontation in decades." |
| s02-blockade | "A full naval blockade of Iranian ports and the Strait of Hormuz took effect yesterday. President Trump warned that any approaching vessel would be, quote, immediately eliminated." |
| s03-talks | "This follows the collapse of twenty-one hours of marathon negotiations in Islamabad. The United States demanded a twenty-year freeze on uranium enrichment. Iran offered five." |
| s04-oil | "Global markets responded immediately. Brent crude surged seven percent to one hundred four dollars per barrel. The IMF has downgraded growth forecasts for the entire Middle East." |
| s05-iran | "Tehran has condemned the blockade as an act of piracy and warned of forceful retaliation against Persian Gulf ports. The Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps remains on high alert." |
| s06-world | "France and the United Kingdom are organizing a naval escort conference. Pakistan has offered to host a second round of negotiations, with Turkey and Egypt acting as mediators." |
| s07-reddit | "Public sentiment reflects deep concern. Online communities describe the escalation as reckless, questioning whether the administration is bypassing congressional war authorization." |
| s08-countdown | "The ceasefire expires on April twenty-first. Seven days remain. This story is developing. Follow for verified updates." |

